Mark Brown writes: As music director of Guildford since 1962, Vernon "Tod" Handley (necrology, September 11) had in charge of the Guildford Philharmonic Orchestra and the choir.
As a member of his music scheme for the municipality, the following year he founded his wonderful youth choir, Proteus.
They were supposed to be under-21s under 21s, but by the time Proteus sang his final in 1979, many of us were more than 20s — we simply refused to give up the chorus.
